# Spec-driven documentation

Use the **default `docs/` tree** below unless the repository already standardizes a different layout (if so, follow the repo and mention the mapping in `docs/README.md`).

## Canonical layout

```text
docs/
  README.md
  planning/
    roadmap.md
    features.md
    ideas.md
  architecture/
    system-overview.md
    folder-structure.md
    integrations.md
  decisions/
    adr-001-<title>.md
    adr-002-<title>.md
  specs/
    <feature-name>/
      spec.md
      plan.md
      tasks.md
      rollout.md
      test-cases.md
  runbooks/
    local-development.md
    release.md
    incident-response.md
  references/
    api.md
    domain-glossary.md
```

### `docs/README.md`

- Entry point: what lives where, how specs and ADRs are written, and links to this rule or team handbook.

### `docs/planning/`

- **`roadmap.md`** — product or engineering roadmap: horizons, milestones, themes, and rough sequencing (not a substitute for per-feature **`spec.md`**—link out to **`docs/specs/<feature>/`**).
- **`features.md`** — **feature inventory**: table or list with status (e.g. idea / planned / in progress / shipped), owner or area, and links to **`docs/specs/<feature>/`** when a spec exists.
- **`ideas.md`** — unstructured or light backlog: candidate features and improvements to triage; promote items to **`features.md`** / **`roadmap.md`** or into a real spec folder when committed.

### `docs/architecture/`

- **System shape** that outlives a single feature: boundaries, major components, integrations.
- Update when cross-cutting structure or external dependencies change—not for every small feature (those go under `docs/specs/<feature>/`).

### `docs/decisions/` (ADRs)

- **Filename:** `adr-<NNN>-<kebab-title>.md` with **three-digit** sequence (`001`, `002`, …) per repository.
- **Content:** context, decision, consequences, alternatives; status (e.g. proposed / accepted / superseded).
- **Superseding:** add a new ADR with a higher number; mark the old one superseded and link both ways.

### `docs/specs/<feature-name>/`

- **Folder name:** `kebab-case`, stable when possible (avoid renaming every time a package name shifts).
- **Files:**
  - **`spec.md`** — problem, goals, non-goals, user-visible behavior, acceptance themes.
  - **`plan.md`** — approach, milestones, technical outline (not a dump of the whole diff).
  - **`tasks.md`** — checklist the team can tick off.
  - **`rollout.md`** — feature flags, migration, rollout order, rollback notes.
  - **`test-cases.md`** — concrete, verifiable scenarios (Given/When/Then or equivalent).

Start with **`spec.md`**; add other files when they add clarity.

### `docs/runbooks/`

- **Operations:** how to develop locally, release, and respond to incidents.
- Update when commands, env vars, or on-call steps change.

### `docs/references/`

- **Long-lived lookups:** API sketches, domain glossary—material that is not a single feature spec and not an ADR.

## When code changes

- Map the change to the right doc:
  - Feature behavior → `docs/specs/<feature>/` (usually `spec.md`, `rollout.md`, or `test-cases.md`).
  - Roadmap or feature list out of date → `docs/planning/roadmap.md` or `docs/planning/features.md` (e.g. status, shipped dates, links).
  - Cross-system or integration boundary → `docs/architecture/` or `docs/references/`.
  - Irreversible architectural choice → new or updated ADR in `docs/decisions/`.
  - Operator-facing steps → `docs/runbooks/`.

## Lightweight review checklist

- [ ] User-visible or API behavior is reflected in **`spec.md`** or **`references/`** as appropriate.
- [ ] Rollout and risk are covered if the change ships progressively (**`rollout.md`**).
- [ ] Tests or verification paths match **`test-cases.md`** (or the spec links to where they live).
- [ ] ADR added or updated if the team is locking a significant design decision.
- [ ] **`planning/features.md`** or **`planning/roadmap.md`** updated if the change affects advertised roadmap or feature status.

---

Prefer **small, accurate edits** over duplicating the same paragraph in three files; link between `spec.md`, `plan.md`, and code where it helps.
